# Programmable Voice

Make and receive voice calls through Twilio's Programmable Voice API. Calls are controlled with TwiML (see [[twilio/twiml]]) which provides verbs for speaking text, playing audio, gathering input, recording, and routing.

## Making an Outbound Call

```javascript
const twilio = require("twilio");

const client = twilio(
  process.env.TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID,
  process.env.TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN
);

const call = await client.calls.create({
  to: "+15551234567",
  from: process.env.TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER,
  twiml: "<Response><Say>Hello! This is an automated call from your agent.</Say></Response>",
});

console.log(call.sid); // CA...
console.log(call.status); // "queued"
```

Alternatively, provide a `url` that returns TwiML dynamically:

```javascript
const call = await client.calls.create({
  to: "+15551234567",
  from: process.env.TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER,
  url: "https://example.com/voice/outbound",
  statusCallback: "https://example.com/voice/status",
});
```

## Receiving Inbound Calls

Configure a webhook URL on your Twilio phone number (Phone Numbers > Active Numbers > Voice). When a call comes in, Twilio requests TwiML from your endpoint:

```javascript
const express = require("express");
const { VoiceResponse } = require("twilio").twiml;

const app = express();
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: false }));

app.post("/voice/inbound", (req, res) => {
  const twiml = new VoiceResponse();
  twiml.say({ voice: "alice" }, "Welcome! Press 1 for sales, 2 for support.");
  const gather = twiml.gather({
    numDigits: 1,
    action: "/voice/menu",
  });
  res.type("text/xml").send(twiml.toString());
});
```

## Recording Calls

Record an entire call or a segment using the `<Record>` TwiML verb (see [[twilio/twiml#voice-verbs]]):

```javascript
app.post("/voice/record", (req, res) => {
  const twiml = new VoiceResponse();
  twiml.say("Please leave a message after the beep.");
  twiml.record({
    maxLength: 60,
    action: "/voice/recording-complete",
    transcribe: true,
  });
  res.type("text/xml").send(twiml.toString());
});
```

## Conference Calls

Connect multiple parties into a conference room:

```javascript
app.post("/voice/conference", (req, res) => {
  const twiml = new VoiceResponse();
  const dial = twiml.dial();
  dial.conference({
    startConferenceOnEnter: true,
    endConferenceOnExit: false,
  }, "MyConferenceRoom");
  res.type("text/xml").send(twiml.toString());
});
```

## Status Callbacks

Track call lifecycle by setting `statusCallback` on call creation. Twilio POSTs updates for: `initiated`, `ringing`, `answered`, `completed` (or `busy`, `no-answer`, `canceled`, `failed`). The callback includes `CallSid`, `CallStatus`, `CallDuration`, and `Direction`.
